One design principle I’d add to the Pantheon is this:

Look for systems that create value by increasing everyone else’s bandwidth.

If your software consistently gives every employee back 20 minutes a day, or helps leaders avoid one major strategic mistake each year, that’s a much stronger moat than simply answering questions. It becomes part of how the organization thinks.

That strikes me as a promising direction because it aligns with the theme we’ve revisited many times: preserving and improving decision capability, not just storing information.